    "Claiming oxygen is 'pumped' into the blood. Gas exchange is passive diffusion down a concentration gradient.",
    "Saying we breathe out 'no oxygen' or 'pure carbon dioxide'. Exhaled air is still about 16% oxygen and only about 4% carbon dioxide.",
    "Forgetting that nitrogen is the biggest part of air (~78%) and is unchanged by breathing.",
    "Saying limewater 'goes clear' for carbon dioxide. It starts clear and turns cloudy/milky when CO2 is present.",
